#import "../../knot-typst-package/lib.typ": *
#show: codly-init

= Cache Invalidation Test

This tests that changing plot options invalidates the cache.

== Initial Plot

```{r plot-test}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
library(ggplot2)

gg <- ggplot(iris, aes(x = Sepal.Length, y = Sepal.Width)) +
  geom_point()

# Second compilation: width=10, height=6 (changed!)
typst(gg, width=10, height=6)
```

Now change the line above to `typst(gg, width=10, height=6)` and recompile.
The cache should be invalidated and a new plot should be generated!
